# Day 11 – Testing and Asynchronous Processing

## Why Testing Matters

Testing is an essential part of software development that ensures applications function correctly before deployment. In Salesforce, testing validates Apex classes, triggers, Flows, and integrations to prevent issues in production environments.

### Benefits of Testing

* Identifies bugs before deployment.
* Ensures business requirements are met.
* Improves application quality and reliability.
* Prevents regressions when new features are added.
* Increases user confidence.
* Required for Salesforce deployment (minimum 75% Apex code coverage).

### Salesforce Testing Features

* Apex Test Classes
* Test.startTest()
* Test.stopTest()
* Assertions
* Mock Data Creation
* Code Coverage Reports

### Example Test Method

```apex
@isTest
private class AccountTest {

    @isTest
    static void testAccountCreation() {

        Account acc = new Account(Name='Test Account');

        insert acc;

        System.assertNotEquals(null, acc.Id);
    }
}
```

