# Important Test Cases

## Test Case 1: Account Record Creation

### Objective

Verify that account records are created successfully.

### Expected Result

Account record exists in the database.

---

## Test Case 2: Validation Rule Testing

### Objective

Verify validation rules prevent invalid data.

### Expected Result

Record save operation fails when invalid values are entered.

---

## Test Case 3: Trigger Testing

### Objective

Verify trigger executes expected business logic.

### Expected Result

Fields update correctly after trigger execution.

---

## Test Case 4: Future Method Testing

### Objective

Verify asynchronous future methods execute correctly.

### Example

```apex
Test.startTest();

MyFutureClass.processData();

Test.stopTest();
```

### Expected Result

Future method completes successfully.

---

## Test Case 5: Queueable Apex Testing

### Objective

Verify queueable jobs execute properly.

### Expected Result

Queued jobs complete and update records correctly.

---

## Test Case 6: Batch Apex Testing

### Objective

Verify large data processing.

### Expected Result

All records are processed successfully.

---

## Test Case 7: Scheduled Apex Testing

### Objective

Verify scheduled jobs run correctly.

### Expected Result

Scheduled job executes without errors.

---

# Async Use Cases

Asynchronous processing is widely used in enterprise Salesforce applications.

## Use Case 1: Sending Emails

When large numbers of emails need to be sent, asynchronous processing prevents delays for users.

### Example

* Welcome Emails
* Marketing Emails
* Notification Emails

---

## Use Case 2: External API Integrations

Salesforce can communicate with external systems without slowing user interactions.

### Example

* Payment Gateway Integration
* ERP Integration
* Third-Party CRM Synchronization

---

## Use Case 3: Large Data Processing

Batch Apex processes thousands or millions of records efficiently.

### Example

* Data Migration
* Data Cleanup
* Mass Updates

---

## Use Case 4: Scheduled Reports

Scheduled Apex automatically generates reports at predefined intervals.

### Example

* Daily Sales Reports
* Weekly Performance Reports
* Monthly Revenue Reports

---

## Use Case 5: Background Calculations

Complex calculations can run without affecting application performance.

### Example

* Revenue Calculations
* Forecasting
* Analytics Processing

