# Reliability Discussion

Reliability refers to the ability of a system to consistently perform its intended functions without failure.

### How Testing Improves Reliability

* Detects defects early.
* Ensures business rules work correctly.
* Validates integrations.
* Reduces production incidents.
* Improves software quality.

### How Asynchronous Processing Improves Reliability

* Prevents user interface slowdowns.
* Handles large workloads efficiently.
* Reduces system bottlenecks.
* Improves scalability.
* Supports fault-tolerant processing.

### Enterprise Benefits

* Better user experience.
* Higher availability.
* Improved performance.
* Easier maintenance.
* Increased customer satisfaction.

