This exercise helped me understand the importance of testing and asynchronous processing in Salesforce development.

### Key Learnings

* Testing ensures software quality and stability.
* Apex test classes validate business logic before deployment.
* Asynchronous processing improves performance by running tasks in the background.
* Future Methods, Queueable Apex, Batch Apex, and Scheduled Apex each serve different business needs.
* Reliable applications require both strong testing strategies and efficient background processing.

### Conclusion

Enterprise Salesforce applications must handle large amounts of data, automation, and user interactions efficiently. Testing ensures correctness, while asynchronous processing improves scalability and performance. Together, they create reliable, maintainable, and high-quality software solutions that support business growth and customer satisfaction.
